    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA328-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu tōḻi varaiviṭai āṟṟāḷākiya talaimakaḷai vaṟpuṟuttatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante encouraged HER who was unable to bear it in the time of marriage.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA328">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            kiḻaṅkukīḻ vīḻntu tēṉmēṟ ṟūṅkic</l>
<l>            ciṟcila vittip paṟpala viḷaintu</l>
<l>            tiṉaikiḷi kaṭiyum peruṅkaṉ ṉāṭaṉ</l>
<l>            piṟappō raṉmai yaṟintaṉa mataṉā</l>
<l>            latuviṉi vāḻi tōḻi yorunāṭ</l>
<l>            ciṟupal karuvit tāki valaṉērpu</l>
<l>            perumpeya ṟalaika puṉaṉē yiṉiyē</l>
<l>            yeṇpiḻi neyyoṭu veṇkiḻi vēṇṭātu</l>
<l>            cāntutalaik koṇṭa vōṅkuperuñ cāral</l>
<l>            vilaṅkumalai yaṭukat tāṉuṅ</l>
<l>            kalampeṟu viṟali yāṭumiv vūrē.</l>
 </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>We knew we were not one in birth<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">piṟappu ōr aṉmai</term> (literally "the non-existence of oneness in birth"): T.V.G. reads this as an acknowledgement of social inferiority on part of the woman. Is the implication, then, that HE is a worthy candidate to be impressed by HER on the next festival occasion?</note></l>
<l rend="indent4">with the man from a land of big stones,</l>
<l rend="indent">where they chase away parrots from the millet,</l>
<l rend="indent">where bulbous roots are extending below<note place="foot">For this strange usage of <term xml:lang="ta">vīḻ</term> in connection with <term xml:lang="ta">kīḻ</term> see <term xml:lang="ta">Kal</term>. 49.11.</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent">honey[-combs] hanging above,</l>
<l rend="indent">where they sow little little [and] reap very much.</l>
<l rend="indent4">Therefore,</l>
<l>that now, oh friend, [is] the one day:</l>
<l rend="indent2">being of small many amounts, rising with strength,</l>
<l>let great rain fall liberally on the fields.</l>
<l rend="indent4">Now,</l>
<l>in this village the dancing girl will be dancing, obtaining ornaments</l>
<l rend="indent2">on all sides(?) of the transverse mountain,</l>
<l rend="indent2">on the high huge slope, grown abundantly with sandal,</l>
<l rend="indent">not needing the white cloth with oil pressed out from sesame.(?)<note place="foot">There are probably implications of cultural significance here that, for the time being, seem irretrievable.</note></l>
        </lg>
      </div>
